0.title: SPACE Data Structure Visualizer

1.title: Installation

11.body: SPACE.hpp contains two main functions. The space::sout() function is used by the student in their programs to output their data structures into a data.json file. The space::save() function is used by the SPACE.hpp program to take the output of space::sout(), convert it to JSON, and output it into a data.json file. The student never uses space::save() in their program.

3.body: This chapter contains the design documents for the SPACE program.
3.title: Design

5.body: The general layout of our application is a main visualization area on the right with a sidebar on the left.
5.title: Overview

6.body: The user may drag a data.json file from their file explorer into the webpage. The data structures saved in the data.json file will populate the side bar. To visualize a data structure, click one of the elements in the side bar. This will fill the visualization pane with a view of that data structure.
6.title: Functionality

7.body: Hover your mouse over an element to see its value. Use the media controls at the bottom to play/pause automatic iteration through the save states of your structure. Use the bar to scrub through the save states of your structure.
7.breadcrumbs: Design documents » UI/UX » The visualization pane
7.title: The visualization pane

8.body: The sidebar contains a list of all data structures present in the data.json file. Clicking on one will open it in the visualization pane. Only one data structure may be visualized at a time. You can open the SPACE manual by clicking the button at the bottom of the side bar.
8.breadcrumbs: Design documents » UI/UX » The side bar
8.title: The side bar

9.body: Each datastructure is an object. They main key for each object will be what the students variable name for that datastructure is e.g. pos_int[] is saved into the JSON file as an object with the name pos_int. Each object will have a type key and data key. The type key defines what type of datastructure the object is. The data key contains the contents of that datastructure. Every time a datastructure is saved, the contents of the datastructure are saved as an array in its JSON object. If multiple saves of the same datastructure occur, each datastructure save array is appened to the data key.
